ngs of a similar kind; the degree of excellence.\"", "\"EXCELLENCE\":\"Excellence is the quality of being outstanding or extremely good.\"", "\"STANDARD\":\"A standard is a level of quality or attainment.\"", "\"LEVEL\":\"A level is a specific height or line, often used to measure or compare.\"", "\"HEIGHT\":\"Height is the measurement of someone or something from head to foot or from base to top.\"", "\"MEASUREMENT\":\"Measurement is the size, length, or amount of something, as established by measuring.\"", "\"SIZE\":\"Size is the relative extent of something; a thing's overall dimensions or magnitude.\"", "\"DIMENSIONS\":\"Dimensions\" are measurable extents of some kind, such as length, breadth, depth, or height. Additionally, dimensions can refer to the aspects of performance that must be measured. In the Fitzgerald and Moon model, there are six specific dimensions: financial performance, competitiveness, quality, resource utilization, flexibility, and innovation."], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}